Here's an example of how to render a table with 10,000 data points using JavaScript:

1. First, prepare your HTML file to have a container element where you will insert your table:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>JavaScript Table Rendering</title>
</head>
<body>
  <div id="table-container"></div>
  <script src="script.js"></script> <!-- Your JavaScript code -->
</body>
</html>
```

2. Next, create a JavaScript file (e.g. script.js) that will render and insert the table into the HTML file:

```javascript
// Generate and return a sample 2-dimensional array of data values
function generateSampleData(rows, cols) {
  const data = [];

  for (let i = 0; i < rows; i++) {
    const rowData = [];

    for (let j = 0; j < cols; j++) {
      rowData.push(`Data-${i}-${j}`);
    }
    data.push(rowData);
  }

  return data;
}

// Render a table element from the given data
function renderTable(data) {
  const table = document.createElement('table');
  table.style.borderCollapse = 'collapse';
  table.style.width = '100%';

  for (let i = 0; i < data.length; i++) {
    const row = document.createElement('tr');

    for (let j = 0; j < data[i].length; j++) {
      const cell = document.createElement('td');
      cell.textContent = data[i][j];

      // Set cell style
      cell.style.border = '1px solid #ccc';
      cell.style.padding = '8px';

      row.appendChild(cell);
    }

    table.appendChild(row);
  }

  return table;
}

// Create an the data, render a table, and insert it into the container
function createAndInsertTable() {
  const data = generateSampleData(100, 100); // (rows, cols)
  const table = renderTable(data);
  const container = document.getElementById('table-container');
  container.appendChild(table);
}

// Call the createAndInsertTable function once the DOM is loaded
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', createAndInsertTable);
```

In this example, a 2-dimensional array of 10,000 data points is generated by `generateSampleData(rows, cols)` function. 

The `renderTable(data)` function takes the data array as input and creates a table structure to display the data. 

Finally, the `createAndInsertTable` function is called when the DOM is ready, which generates the data, renders the table and inserts it into the `table-container` element in the HTML file. You can change the rows and cols value in createAndInsertTable function to generate the different number of data points.

